article_title: Obamacare Exchanges Attract Few High Income Americans

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: Government-run exchanges have been good at attracting low income Americans to subsidized coverage under the Affordable Care Act, but aren’t attracting higher income buyers who could be needed in the future, according to a new analysis.
